What is the solution set of the equation |x - 4| = 8?

Choose from:
 a). {3,11}
 b). {-3,11}
 c). {-3,-11}
 d). {3,-11}
The answer is:

a). {3,11}

The solution set of the equation |x - 4| = 8 is {3,11}. This is because the absolute value of |x - 4| = 8 means that x - 4 can be either 8 or -8. Therefore, x can be either 11 or 3.

